'''Eastern Kentucky University''', commonly referred to as '''Eastern''' or by the acronym '''EKU''' by local residents, is an undergraduate and graduate teaching and research institution located in [[Richmond, Kentucky]], [[United States of America|U.S.A.]]. EKU is accredited by the [[Southern Association of Colleges and Schools]] (SACS)<ref>SACS http://www.sacscoc.org/searchResults.asp</ref> with regional campuses in [[Corbin, Kentucky|Corbin]], [[Danville, Kentucky|Danville]], and [[Manchester, Kentucky|Manchester]], and centers in [[Fort Knox]], [[Lancaster, Kentucky|Lancaster]], and [[Somerset, Kentucky|Somerset]]<ref>[http://www.eku.edu/campuses Continuing Education and Outreach - List of EKU Campuses and Centers]</ref>.
